140
00:07:10,884 --> 00:07:12,725
The first is that brains are incredibly stubborn.

141
00:07:13,465 --> 00:07:17,887
We are not, at the best of times, very good at fighting our natural tendencies.

142
00:07:17,907 --> 00:07:21,168
Have you ever tried to break a habit? Have you ever tried to quit smoking?

143
00:07:21,368 --> 00:07:24,389
Or, you know, whatever, say um too much while you're talking?

144
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:27,151
All of these things are incredibly difficult to do.

145
00:07:28,091 --> 00:07:29,772
We're worse when we're in a flow state,

146
00:07:29,792 --> 00:07:31,632
which is hopefully where our players are going to be.

147
00:07:34,693 --> 00:07:37,275
Our brains are hardwired to find patterns.

148
00:07:37,335 --> 00:07:38,835
We can't help it.

149
00:07:40,050 --> 00:07:44,394
As a culture, we talk about stereotypes as being an incredibly negative thing, but there's

150
00:07:44,434 --> 00:07:45,835
